info.headline: High Wind Warning issued February 24 at 1:33PM MST until February 25 at 5:00PM MST by NWS Cheyenne
info.description: ...HIGH WIND WARNING IN EFFECT FROM 11 PM THIS EVENING TO 5 PM MST SATURDAY... * WHAT...Southwest winds 25 to 35 mph with gusts up to 60 mph possible. Blowing snow may create visibility reductions less than one mile at times. * WHERE...North Snowy Range Foothills, including the Arlington and Elk Mountain area along Interstate-80. * WHEN...From 11PM this evening through 5PM Saturday afternoon. * IMPACTS...Mainly to transportation. Strong cross winds will be hazardous to light weight or high profile vehicles, including campers and tractor trailers.
info.instruction: A High Wind Warning means a hazardous high wind event is expected or occurring. Sustained wind speeds of at least 40 mph or gusts of 58 mph or more can lead to property damage.
